@Zheratul No. I'm arguing that the words millionaire, billionaire, trillionaire, whatever-aire have a definition and it's about a person's assets not their income.

A millionaire is a person with a million dollars in assets. A person with a ten million dollar income with 0 dollars in assets, somehow, isn't a millionaire.

I didn't say one is better off than the other. I said one of them is a millionaire and the other isn't.
